Search help

Course no.

You can include more than one course number in the search by separating these with a comma. (ex. 01005,01227,02105)

Search word

If your search includes more than one word, your search result will include all of the courses that contains one of these words. If you wish to search for a sentence, use quotation marks at the beginning and end of the sentence (ex. “complex numbers”)

If you use a course number as a search word, you will be shown all of the courses, where the course is mentioned. This way you can find the courses related to a specific course.

Course type

Some courses might occur with several course types, e.g. “BSc/MSC”, “Advanced”, and “General competence course” Courses can be found by searching just one of these course types.

Teaching language

It is possible to search specifically for courses taught in English or in Danish

Study planner

You can search for courses and put them into your course basket in the Course-search. If you log on to the Study planner, the courses that you have put into your basket will be transferred to your Study-planner basket. From here, you can move the courses around, and into the different semesters.
